The use and effectiveness of spring lock washers has been in debate of late&#44[when?] with some publications[who?] advising against their use on the grounds that&#44 when tight&#44 the washer is flat against the substrate and gives no more resistance to rotation than a normal washer at the same torque
material - spring steel&#44 finish - zinc/clear

Spring washers are a left hand helix and allow the thread to be tightened in a right hand direction only&#44 i.e. a clockwise direction. When a left hand turning motion is applied&#44 the raised edge bites into the underside of the bolt or nut and the part that it is bolted to&#44 thus resisting turning. Therefore&#44 spring washers are ineffective on left hand threads and hardened surfaces. Also&#44 they are not to be used in conjunction with a flat washer under the spring washer&#44 as this isolates the spring washer from biting into the component that will resist turning. Where a flat washer is required to span a large hole in a component&#44 a nyloc nut (nylon insert) must be used.

The use and effectiveness of spring lock washers has been in debate of late&#44[when?] with some publications[who?] advising against their use on the grounds that&#44 when tight&#44 the washer is flat against the substrate and gives no more resistance to rotation than a normal washer at the same torque
z/clear

Spring washers are a left hand helix and allow the thread to be tightened in a right hand direction only&#44 i.e. a clockwise direction. When a left hand turning motion is applied&#44 the raised edge bites into the underside of the bolt or nut and the part that it is bolted to&#44 thus resisting turning. Therefore&#44 spring washers are ineffective on left hand threads and hardened surfaces. Also&#44 they are not to be used in conjunction with a flat washer under the spring washer&#44 as this isolates the spring washer from biting into the component that will resist turning. Where a flat washer is required to span a large hole in a component&#44 a nyloc nut (nylon insert) must be used.

Spray is a wax based, solvent cutback, amber colored corrosion preventive compound which is supplied in an aerosol spray can.
Has good water displacing properties and good penetration, making it very suitable as a versatile corrosion protective providing a wide variety of applications: Automotive, Marine, Household and Industrial.
Cures to an amber colored, waxy, semi-firm translucent film.
Application:- gives a maximum performance when it is sprayed at an ambient and product temperature of 10-25 °C.
Shake the can well before use and spray at a distance of approximately 25 cm from the surface.
As the is a fast drying product this can cause “pin-holing” when the product is applied too thick at once. Valvoline advises to spray one layer per pass, wait for 2 to 3 minutes and then spray another layer. Continue like this until the required film thickness has been obtained.
Storage: should be stored at temperatures between 10-35 °C. Shaking the can well prior to use is recommended. For storage after use invert the can and spray for a few seconds to clear the nozzle.
The container is pressurized. Keep away from flammable substances and protect from direct sunlight and temperatures over 50°C. Under proper storage conditions can have a shelf life of 3 years minimum.

Power Can Wheel Silver is a 1K ready to use metallic coating in an aerosol. It is used for refinishing primed/metal surfaces in order to achieve a uniform light shade metallic finish.
Power Can Wheel Silver is capable of producing a coating of a film thickness similar to that of a spray gun applied topcoat. The convenience of using a high build coating in an aerosol means that masking is kept to a minimum. Mixing paint and cleaning spray equipment are avoided as a result of using Power Can Wheel Silver leading to savings in time and materials.
Power Can Wheel Silver is isocyanate free.

Power Can Satin Black is capable of producing a coating of a film thickness similar to that of a spray gun applied topcoat. The convenience of using a high build coating in an aerosol means that masking is kept to a minimum. Mixing paint and cleaning spray equipment are avoided as a result of using Power Can Satin Black leading to savings in time and materials. Power Can Satin Black is isocyanate free.

Thoroughly clean and degrease surfaces with Precleaner or panel prep such as U-POL System 20 Degreaser. Abrade primed surfaces wet with 600-800 or dry with 400-600 abrasive, re-clean, dry and degrease.
Shake can thoroughly before use for a minimum of 2 minutes.
Apply 1-2 light even coats.
Allow 3-5 minutes flash off time between coats.
For optimum gloss and durability overcoat with Power Can Clear Coat, do so within a period of 20-60 minutes after application of the Power Can Steel Wheels. Drying time is dependent upon film thickness, humidity and temperature.

The EU limit for this product (product category: IIBe) in ready to use form is 840g/litre.
The VOC content of this product in ready to use form is 665g/litre.

Power Can Steel Wheels is a 1K ready to use metallic coating in an aerosol. It is used for refinishing primed/metal surfaces in order to achieve a uniform dark shade metallic finish.
Power Can Steel Wheels is capable of producing a coating of a film thickness similar to that of a spray gun applied topcoat. The convenience of using a high build coating in an aerosol means that masking is kept to a minimum. Mixing paint and cleaning spray equipment are avoided as a result of using Power Can Steel Wheels leading to savings in time and materials.
Power Can Steel Wheels is isocyanate free.

TIGER SEAL PU sealant and adhesive can be used on the following surfaces:
- Steel, aluminium, brass, iron.
- Fibre Glass and most plastics.
- Glass, Wood, Ceramics, Paint
Surfaces should be clean, dry and free from grease.
Apply with a standard cartridge caulking gun or pneumatic version at approximately 6 bar (108psi).
Drying Time: 30-60 mins to skin.
Through cure of approximately 3mm per 24 hours.
All results at 23°C and 50% relative humidity.
Over Painting: TIGER SEAL may be over-painted with most paint systems once fully cured. Can be over-painted once it has skinned if using 2K polyurethane paints.
The drying of synthetic paint may be retarded. Household gloss will not dry over this product.
The VOC content of this product in ready to use form is 113g/litre.

A simple and effective small parts storage system for a wide range of materials.

Space saving, manufactured from polypropylene, can be stacked or for increased flexibility, used with Topstore Louvred Panels, Cabinets and Shelving.

Strong, heavy duty with reinforced base, sides and stacking rim
Durable, resistant to most industrial solvents
Material is capable of withstanding a temperature range from -15 degrees C to +50 degrees C. However this may not apply when under load or stress dependant upon use or application
Hygienc, clean, smooth inside faces guard against build up of grease etc.
Index card slot for product identification (labels not supplied as standard please order separately)

Important: Container Stacking Loads

Please note that when stacking containers, the entire stack load is dispersed onto the base container.

Therefore neither the individual load or the total load of the stacked containers (up to the max.stack height) should exceed the maximum stack load.

The diagram shows TC5 containers stacked to their maximum of 4 high.

As the maximum stack load for TC5 is 45Kg, if containers 1ƺ &3 are equally loaded they can each carry 15Kg.

If they were stacked 3 high and equally loaded each container could carry 22.5Kg or 2 high 45Kg.

The unique combination of properties in Delta Copper Anti-Seize ensures rapid and easy assembly of threaded parts. It allows correct torque to be applied by eliminating thread interference. By protecting against seizure&#44 maintenance work requiring routine or infrequent assembly and dismantling is made much easier and less costly.

GRAVIGARD stone chip protector can be used on the following surfaces:-
- Suitably prepared, primed or bare metal.
For overcoating aluminium, an etch primer is recommended.- Original paint surfaces (with the exception of thermoplastic acrylics).
Thoroughly clean and degrease old paint surfaces with a suitable spirit wipe or thinner. Wet flat with 400 grade paper. For bare metal use 180 grade paper. Re-clean and dry.
Shake the can before use. Spray the GRAVIGARD at a distance of 20-30 cm from the panel being coated.
Build: One coat of GRAVIGARD will give a build of approximately 35 microns. Varying the distance of the can from the panel during spraying will give a flatter or bumpier effect. When building a thick coat, allow approximately 10-15 mins. between coats for the solvent to flash off.
Drying Time: Approximately 2 hours at normal shop temperature or 30 mins. at low bake (80ºC). Drying time is dependent on film thickness, humidity and temperature.
Over Painting: GRAVIGARD may be over-painted with most paint systems. With 2 pack acrylic paints it can be over-painted wet-on-wet. For optimum gloss the use of a primer is recommended.

For aerosols the EU limit for this product (product category: IIBe) in ready to use form is 840g/litre.
For aerosols the VOC content of this product in ready to use form is 600g/litre.

GRAVIGARD is a durable coating designed to reproduce the manufacturer's original stone chip finish. GRAVIGARD will protect against stone chips, salt, damp and rust.
GRAVIGARD will also help to deaden sound and vibrations and is, therefore, ideal for application to body panels and inside engine compartments. The high build formula will cover weld marks and seams, often in one application.

Cleaning of spark plugs and injectors.
Dismantling of injectors and spark plugs stuck by rust and dirt.

1. Shake can well before use. Remove loose dirt around the
injectors and / or spark plugs with compressed air.
2. Spray a generous amount on the total surface area and leave
the product on for approximately 40 minutes for the best results.
Removes loose dirt with compressed air.
3. Spray again, however direct the product on the injector seat, or
the spark plug. Leave on for approximately 5 minutes.
4. Remove the injector with an injector tractor and / or remove the
spark plug.

Intensive rust remover.
Provides extreme cooling causing micro-cracks in the rust layer.
Good penetration properties, as active ingredients penetrate
the micro cracks deep in the rust layer and dissolve the rust.
Loosens stuck spark plugs and injectors for disassembly.
Provides rapid results without causing damage.
Removes rust, thick dirt and oil from spark plugs and injectors.
PTFE particles improve the mechanical properties and
ease disassembly.
Displaces water and prevents new rust formation.
Free of acids and Silicone.
